I'm afraid I couldn't find a clear list of mayors of Philadelphia, PA, but I did find some information about the 2003 and 2023 mayoral elections. 

The 2003 election was won by John Street, who served as mayor of Philadelphia from 2000 to 2008. He was succeeded by Michael Nutter, who served from 2008 to 2016. 

Then, in the 2023 election, Jim Kenney won and became the mayor of Philadelphia, taking office on January 2, 2024. 

Would you like to know more about these mayors and their time in office?
